    "comment": "Rationale: \"Syndecan-2 is important for dendritic spine formation\". Knockdown with shRNA reduces formation of protrusions from dendrites (Fig. 1). Syndecan-2 positive protrusion opposed by structures contained the presynaptic marker synaptophysin (Fig. 10A). Syndecan-2 acts via neurofibromin-Ena/VASP signaling pathway on dendritic spinogenesis (Fig. 10). Experimental description: Hippocampal neuronal cultures were performed as described previously\n(Wang et al., 2004; Lin et al., 2006). In the former paper it is mentioned that \"Hippocampal neurons from embryonic day 18-20 rat brains were dissociated and cultured in Neurobasal medium,...\" PMID: 15066269",
